==Listen-at Grill==
* '''Black Knight Captain:''' So... how's the secret weapon coming along?
* '''Witch:''' The invincibility potion is almost ready...
* '''Witch:''' It's taken me FIVE YEARS, but it's almost ready.
* '''Witch:''' Greldo the Goblin here is just going to fetch the last ingredient for me.
* '''Witch:''' It's a specially grown cabbage grown by my cousin Helda who lives in Draynor Manor.
* '''Witch:''' The soil there is slightly magical and it gives the cabbages slight magical properties....
* '''Witch:''' ...not to merntion the trees!
* '''Witch:''' Now remember Greldo, only a Draynor Manor cabbage will do! Don't get lazy and bring any old cabbage, THAT would ENTIRELY wreck the potion!
* '''Greldo:''' Yeth, Mithreth.
* {{tact|end}}

==Reporting back to Sir Amik Varze==
* '''Sir Amik Varze:''' How's the mission going?
* '''Player:''' I've found out what the Black Knight's secret weapon is. It's a potion of invincibility.
* '''Sir Amik Varze:''' A potion of invincibility? That is grave news indeed. If you can sabotage it somehow, you will be very well paid.
* '''Player:''' So when I finish this mission for you can I be a white knight? Can I wear your armour too?
* '''Sir Amik Varze:''' I am afraid I cannot authorise you to become a white knight unless under a situation of dire circumstance. Assisting us on a freelance basis will be well worth your time however and you will have my personal gratitude.
* '''Player:''' I can't buy stuff with personal gratitude though...
* '''Sir Amik Varze:''' There is of course also the financial recompense as I said.
* '''Player:''' Ok! I'll get on to sabotaging that potion.
* {{tact|end}}

==Sabotaging the potion==
===Interrupting the Black Knights' meeting===
* '''Fortress Guard:''' I wouldn't go in there if I were you. Those Black Knights are in an important meeting. They said they'd kill anyone who went in there!
* {{tselect|Select an Option}}
* {{topt|Okay, I won't.}}
** '''Player:''' Okay, I won't.
** '''Fortress Guard:''' Wise move.
** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|I don't care. I'm going in anyway.}}
** '''Player:''' I don't care. I'm going in anyway.
** {{tact|end}}

===Using any item on the hole, or a cabbage before overhearing the witch===
* '''Player:''' Why exactly would I want to do that?
* {{tact|end}}

===Using a Draynor cabbage on the hole===
* {{tbox|This is the wrong sort of cabbage!}}
* '''Player:''' I'm not supposed to be HELPING the witch you know...
* {{tact|end}}

===Using a normal cabbage on the hole===
* {{qact|The player throws the cabbage through the hole}}
* '''Witch:''' Where has Greldo got to with that magic cabbage!
* '''Black Knight Captain:''' What's that noise?
* '''Witch:''' Hopefully Greldo with the cabbage... yes, look here it co....NOOOOOoooo!
* {{qact|The cabbage falls through the hole in the ceiling and lands in the potion, destroying it.}}
* '''Witch:''' My potion!
* '''Black Knight Captain:''' Oh boy, this doesn't look good!
* '''Black Cat:''' Meow!<ref name="catspeak">No special dialogue with catspeak amulet equipped</ref>
* '''Player:''' Looks like my work here is done. Seems like that's successfully sabotaged their little secret weapon plan.
* {{tact|end}}

===Listen-at Grill after ruining the potion===
* '''Witch:''' It's RUINED! All that work, FIVE years down the drain, who was it! I'll find them and when I do....
* '''Black Knight Captain:''' Erm.. maybe we can save some of it?
* '''Witch:''' SAVE some of it? Are you mad!? That cabbage was a normal cabbage, it spoilt the whole thing and now I have to start all over again!
* '''Black Knight Captain:''' No need to... get upset... you're scaring the cat.
* '''Witch:''' 'The CAT'? She's not 'THE CAT'! 
* '''Witch:''' She's Maemi... aren't you dear....
* '''Black Cat:''' Purrr....<ref name="catspeak"/>
* {{tact|end}}

==Returning to Sir Amik Varze==
* '''Player:''' I have ruined the Black Knights' invincibility potion. That should put a stop to your problem and an end to their little schemes.
* '''Sir Amik Varze:''' Yes, we have just received a message from the Black Knights saying they withdraw their demands, which would seem to confirm your story.
* '''Player:''' Now I believe there was some talk of a cash reward...
* '''Sir Amik Varze:''' Absolutely right. Please accept this reward.
* {{tbox|Sir Amik hands you 2500 coins.}}
* {{qact|Congratulations! Quest complete!}}

